Abuja (Sundiata Post)  –   Governor  of Ebonyi state, Dave Umahi says he has tested positive for the coronavirus. The Governor made this known in a statement signed by himself on Saturday. According to Umahi, he and some of his close aides tested positive for the virus after carrying out the coronavirus test. Umahi further disclosed that, presently, they are currently asymptomatic but have since isolated, in line with protocols laid down by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The Governor directed the Deputy Governor, Kelechi Igwe, to take over the frontline coordination of the state’s fight against the pandemic to protect Ebonyi people. Umahi appealed to the people of Ebonyi state to take the NCDC protocols more seriously while stating that he’s working from home and will conduct all meetings virtually. Since the pandemic, according to the NCDC, Ebonyi state has recorded 438 cases of the virus, as at Friday evening. Ebonyi Governor David Umahi has tested positive for COVID-19. The Governor made the announcement in a statement he personally signed on Saturday He, however, noted that he is asymptotic and has since isolated himself in line with Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) protocols. He said he has handed over… July 4, 2020 In "News" ABUJA - Seventy-six Nigerians died of COVID-19 in the last week, data from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) have shown. Also, 273 patients died of the disease in the country between May 20 and June 18, 2020. By the close of work on Friday, 12 June 2020, the… June 20, 2020 In "News" By Chukwuemeka Opara Abakaliki - Gov. David Umahi of Ebonyi on Friday announced the first death recorded from the COVID-19 outbreak in the state.The governor, who did not give further information about the victim during a statewide broadcast in Abakaliki, also directed that all courts in the state be shut… June 19, 2020 In "News"